cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.GT 

This paper discusses reinforcement learning with a focus on risk measures and constrained optimization. It is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with RL algorithms and their optimization. It may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as RL is a subfield of AI. Additionally, it may fall under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as RL is often used in robotics and control systems. Finally, it may be categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory) as RL can be used to model and solve game-theoretic problems.
